Bring a large #pot{} of water to the boil. Roughly chop the @mint{1}(leaves chopped). Place the flat-side of a large #knife{} on the @garlic cloves{3} and press down firmly. Peel off the skin and finely chop the garlic.

Cook the @wheat penne pasta{440%g} in the boiling water for ~{10%minutes} with ½ tsp of @salt{1/2%tsp}. Keep 2 tbsp of pasta water before you drain it.

> Tip: Keep some pasta water before draining it.

Brown off the @pine nuts{4} in a #non-stick frying pan{} on medium-high heat. They should take a few mins to start browning but watch them like a hawk as they can burn really easily. Once toasted take them out of the pan and keep them for later.

Heat @olive oil{2%tsp} in the same pan on medium-high heat. Cook the @British smoked bacon lardons{2} until it goes crispy around the edges.

Add in the @peas{1.5%cups} and continue to cook for ~{5%minutes}. Add in the garlic for a further ~{1%minute}.

Add 2 tbsp of water from the pasta to the pan with the peas. Cook for ~{1%minute} before stirring in the @crème fraîche{2%tbsp} together with the @vegetable stock pot{1} and a few good grinds of @black pepper{}.

By now your penne should be ready. Drain it and mix into your sauce together with your chopped mint.

Plate up your pasta, grate the @parmesan cheese{4%tbsp} over the top and sprinkle over your pine nuts. Tuck in and enjoy!